{"title_page": "AEBN", "text_new": "{{short description|Internet pornography company}}\n{{Infobox dot-com company\n| name           = AEBN\n| logo           = Adult Entertainment Broadcast Network.jpg \n| foundation     = {{Start date and age|1999}}\n| location       = [[Charlotte, North Carolina]]\n| alexa          = 2,576  ({{as of|2012|11|alt=November 2012}})<ref name=\"alexa\">{{cite web |url=http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/aebn.net |title=aebn.net Site Info |publisher=[[Alexa Internet]] |accessdate=2012-11-20}}</ref>\n| website_type   = [[Internet pornography|Pornographic]] [[streaming video]]\n| language       = [[English language|English]]\n| registration   = Optional (pay-per-minute)\n| current_status = Active\n| url            = {{URL|aebn.net/}}\n}}\n\n'''AEBN''', short for '''Adult Entertainment Broadcast Network''', is an [[Internet pornography]] company that specializes in delivering material through [[streaming video]] in a [[video on demand]] format. Subsidiaries include PornoTube.\n\n==History==\nAEBN was formed in 1999.<ref name=TakingStock>{{cite web|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/27916.html |title=Taking Stock in the Future: Vision and perseverance pay off for VOD pioneer AEBN |date=1 August 2006 |publisher=Adult Video News |accessdate=6 October 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090827013955/http://business.avn.com/articles/27916.html |archivedate=27 August 2009 }}</ref> At the time, [[streaming media|video-streaming]] technology was still in its infancy.<ref name=TakingStock/> AEBN developed and launched an adult [[Video-on-Demand]] service that now serves as a widely recognized model of content delivery for the [[sex industry|adult industry]].<ref name=TakingStock/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.allbusiness.com/technology/technology-services/246515-1.html |title=Naked Ambition |author=Steve Goldberg and Arthur Murray |date=1 September 2002 |work= |publisher=AllBusiness |accessdate=1 September 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090903070046/http://www.allbusiness.com/technology/technology-services/246515-1.html|archive-date=3 September 2009}}</ref> AEBN's pay-per-minute model is a standard in [[online pornography]]. In 2004, AEBN began offering its theater templates in languages other than English.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=2425 |title=AEBN Pushing International Traffic |author=Rhett Pardon |date=17 March 2004 |work= |publisher=XBIZ |accessdate=7 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304044715/http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=2425 |archive-date=4 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nHeadquartered in [[Charlotte, North Carolina|Charlotte]], [[North Carolina]], AEBN offers more than 100,000 titles and includes material from at least 1,500 different studios with 10 million subscribers worldwide, as of 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.xbiz.com/articles/135346 |title=Company Profile: AEBN\u2019s Empire Still Growing |author=Alex Henderson |date=21 June 2011 |work= |publisher=XBIZ |accessdate=25 October 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Studio and other acquisitions==\n\nIn January 2007, AEBN announced a [[merger]] with NakedSword.com, one of the largest gay Internet pornography companies on the Web. The merger gave AEBN a windfall of gay content from studios such as COLT and Falcon, as well as a strong brand name in the gay market.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=18989 |title=Valenti: NakedSword, AEBN to Share Revenue on VOD |author=Gretchen Gallen |date=10 January 2007 |work= |publisher=XBIZ |accessdate=23 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120301155049/http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=18989 |archive-date=1 March 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> NakedSword retained its separate headquarters in [[San Francisco]], [[California]], giving AEBN offices on both the east and west coasts.\n\nIn 2009, AEBN merged with another gay adult company, [[Raging Stallion Studios]], and its sister label, Pistol Media. The merger also included Pistol Media's Gunzblazing affiliate program. Raging Stallion Studios is also based in San Francisco and is one of the world's largest producers of gay adult films.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://avn.com/business/articles/gay/aebn-nakedsword-merges-with-raging-stallion-pistol-media-304432.html |title=AEBN/NakedSword Merges with Raging Stallion, Pistol Media |author=Benji Featherstone |date=19 February 2009 |work= |publisher=Adult Video News |accessdate=18 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn December 19, 2010, AEBN purchased Falcon Studios for an undisclosed sum.<ref name=RS>{{cite web|url=http://cartcms.ragingstallion.com/photocontent/press/press122010.html |title=AEBN Acquires Falcon Studios and Merges with Raging Stallion |date=19 December 2010 |publisher=Raging Stallion website |accessdate=21 October 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120311071836/http://cartcms.ragingstallion.com/photocontent/press/press122010.html |archivedate=11 March 2012 }}</ref>\n\nAEBN merged Falcon Studios and Raging Stallion, although the company said that both brands would remain distinct and AEBN's output would remain constant at 60 DVD titles per year, with 40 originating from Raging Stallion.<ref name=RS/> Falcon CEO James Hansen would remain with the company as the chief financial officer of Falcon Studios.<ref name=RS/>\n\n==Other ventures==\n\nAEBN launched Xobile in April 2005. Xobile made adult material available on mobile devices.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/10482343 |title=Porn pushing the technology envelope |author= |date=15 December 2005 |work= |publisher=NBC News |accessdate=21 October 2011}}</ref> Xobile was known for its \"PornMyPortable\" campaign, which offered adult material specifically made to work with mobile entertainment devices like the [[iPod]] and [[Sony PSP|Sony's PSP]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.redorbit.com/news/technology/295515/pornmyportabl