nga|work=hindustantimes.com|date=2011-11-20|accessdate=2011-11-20}}</ref> However, she refused to divulge her porn star status, and replied to fellow house-mate [[Pooja Bedi]] that she was a model and a TV star in America for the last ten years or so.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/idiotbox/bigg-boss-sunny-leone-hides-her-porn-star-status_100679.htm|title=Bigg Boss: Sunny Leone hides her porn star status|work=zeenews.india.com|date=2011-11-22|accessdate=2011-11-22}}</ref> It was reported that she caused a stir in the larger populace<ref>{{cite web|url=https://theprovince.com/news/Canadian+porn+star+Sunny+Leone+causes+stir+India/5760537/story.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111128192130/http://www.theprovince.com/news/Canadian%2Bporn%2Bstar%2BSunny%2BLeone%2Bcauses%2Bstir%2BIndia/5760537/story.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=November 28, 2011 |title=Canadian porn star Sunny Leone causes stir in India |work=theprovince.com |date=2011-11-24 |accessdate=2011-11-28 |df= }}</ref> with her Twitter feed gaining 8,000 new followers in just 2 days<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-11-22/tv/30428111_1_contract-star-twitter-users-penthouse-pet |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120707134721/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-11-22/tv/30428111_1_contract-star-twitter-users-penthouse-pet |url-status=dead |archive-date=2012-07-07 |title=Adult star Sunny Leone is trending in India |first=Priya |last=Ramachandran |work=indiatimes.com |date=2011-11-22 |accessdate=2011-11-28}}</ref> and [[Google]] saying searches for her experienced a \"breakout\".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-11-27/tv/30444716_1_sunny-deol-google-trends-search-data |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120707045831/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-11-27/tv/30444716_1_sunny-deol-google-trends-search-data |url-status=dead |archive-date=2012-07-07 |title=Sunny Leone most googled in Orissa, Haryana |work=indiatimes.com |date=2011-11-27 |quote=For a few days the growth in search queries related to Sunny Leone was what Google describes 'breakout'. |accessdate=2011-11-28}}</ref> There were also complaints lodged with the Indian [[Ministry of Information and Broadcasting (India)|Ministry of Information and Broadcasting]] alleging that the [[Colors (TV channel)|Colors]] TV channel was promoting pornography by having Leone appear on the show; among those who filed are the Indian Artistes and Actors Forum<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mediamughals.com/News/1/1/Article/8593/IAAF_files_complaint_against_Colors_for_Sunny_Leone_entry.htm |title=IAAF files complaint against Colors for Sunny Leone entry |first=Anthony |last=Mawrie |work=mediamughals.com |date=2011-11-29 |accessdate=2011-12-02 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111203070208/http://www.mediamughals.com/News/1/1/Article/8593/IAAF_files_complaint_against_Colors_for_Sunny_Leone_entry.htm |archivedate=December 3, 2011 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> and [[Anurag Thakur]], member of [[Lok Sabha]] and head of the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]'s youth wing.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/bjp-leader-tv-channel-sunny-leone-bigg-boss/1/162383.html |title=Sunny Leone in 'Bigg Boss': BJP youth wing president seeks action against Colors : Gossip News&nbsp;\u2014 India Today |first=Aatish |last=Srivastava |work=indiatoday.intoday.in |date=2011-12-01 |accessdate=2011-12-02}}</ref> She was evicted on Day 91.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/porn-star-sunny-leone-to-enter-bigg-boss-146090-2011-11-17|title=Porn star Sunny Leone to enter 'Bigg Boss' house|date=17 November 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/photogallery/tv/sunny-leones-bigg-boss-journey-ends-819259.html|title=Bigg Boss 5: Sunny Leone evicted from the house|date=1 January 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-sunny-leone-on-her-stint-in-bigg-boss-house/20120102.htm#5|title='Juhi is the backbone of the house who keeps everyone together'|date=2 January 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Sunny - Jism 2 01.jpg|thumb|left|Leone on the set of ''[[Jism 2]]'' in 2012]] \nDuring her stay in the ''Bigg Boss'' house, Leone was approached by [[Bollywood]] film-maker [[Mahesh Bhatt]] who entered the house briefly to offer her the lead role in ''[[Jism 2]]'' (the sequel to the 2003 film ''[[Jism (2003 film)|Jism]]''). She accepted it, which resulted in [[Pooja Bhatt]]'s production house, Fish Eye Network and Leone's agent discussing the movie further.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Television/Sunny-Leone-says-yes-to-Mahesh-Bhatt/Article1-776614.aspx |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111202111347/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Television/Sunny-Leone-says-yes-to-Mahesh-Bhatt/Article1-776614.aspx |url-status=dead |archive-date=2011-12-02 |title=Sunny Leone says yes to Mahesh Bhatt&nbsp;\u2014 Hindustan Times |work=hindustantimes.com |year=2011 |accessdate=2011-12-02}}</ref> Leone entered Bollywood in 2012 with the film ''[[Jism 2]]'' to weak critical reception but was commercially successful.<ref name=\"Hindustan Times\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/i-haven-t-made-jism-2-for-100-crore-club-pooja-bhatt/article1-909714.aspx |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120808134027/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/I-haven-t-made-Jism-2-for-100-crore-club-Pooja-Bhatt/Article1-909714.aspx |url-status=dead |archive-date=August 8, 2012 |title=I haven't made Jism 2 for 100 crore club: Pooja Bhatt |publisher=Hindustan Times |accessdate=7 August 2012 |df= }}</ref>\nSunny Leone signed her second Bollywood film,  ''[[Ragini MMS 2]]'', sequel to [[Ekta Kapoor]]'s crossover horror movie ''[[Ragini MMS]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.invectura.com/sunny-leone-in-ragini-mms-2/ |title=Sunny Leone in Ragini MMS 2 |work=invectura.com |date=2012-04-22 |accessdate=2012-04-22}}</ref> Sunny Leone featured in an [[item number]] in the [[Sanjay Gupta]] and [[Ekta Kapoor]]'s 2013 film ''[[Shootout at Wadala]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sunny Leone goes desi for first item song in Bollywood|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Sunny-Leone-goes-desi-for-first-item-song-in-Bollywood/Article1-1021993.aspx|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130307060259/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Sunny-Leone-goes-desi-for-first-item-song-in-Bollywood/Article1-1021993.aspx|url-status=dead|archive-date=7 March 2013|publisher=Hindustan Times|accessdate=6 March 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Check Out: Sunny Leone in Shootout At Wadala|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/4647|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=6 March 2013}}</ref> She further started filming for Kaizad Gustad's ''[[Jackpot (2013 film)|Jackpot]]'' in which she plays a [[femme fatale]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Kaizad Gustad hits the Jackpot|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/more/news/view/id/1855079|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=2 July 2013|date=2013-06-25}}</ref> ''Jackpot'' released on 13 December 2013 and was panned by critics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/598013|title=Jackpot|publisher=|accessdate=September 22, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Ragini MMS 2 and further success (2014\u2013present)===\n[[File:Sunny Leone snapped in Mumbai.jpg|left|thumb|upright|Sunny Leone in 2018 in Mumbai]]\nHer first release of 2014 was the much anticipated horror film ''[[Ragini MMS 2]]'', which proved to be a box-office hit.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/Details/art_detail/toptenworldwidegrossers2014#.U-AH7fl_ssZ|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140508150134/http://boxofficeindia.com/Details/art_detail/toptenworldwidegrossers2014|url-status=dead|archive-date=May 8, 2014|title=Boxoffice|publisher=|accessdate=September 22, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/Movies/movie_detail/ragini_mms_2#.U-AH5vl_ssY |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140401024315/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/Movies/movie_detail/ragini_mms_2 |url-status=dead |archive-date=April 1, 2014 |title=Boxoffice|accessdate=September 22, 2014}}</ref> Leone's performance received all round praise with critic [[Koimoi|Mohar Basu]] calling her work a \"revelation\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koimoi.com/movie/ragini-mms-2/?type=review|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006223634/http://www.koimoi.com/movie/ragini-mms-2/?type=review|url-status=dead|archive-date=October 6, 2014|title=Movie Review:Ragini Mms 2|publisher=|accessdate=September 22, 2014}}</ref> Critic [[Taran Adarsh]] also noted that Leone,  \"carries off her character with supreme confidence\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/551006|title=Ragini MMS \u2013 2|publisher=|accessdate=September 22, 2014}}</ref> In November 2013, she had confirmed that she would make her [[Tamil language|Tamil]] film debut in ''[[Vadacurry]]'' which released in May 2014 and featured her in a special appearance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/news-interviews/Sunny-Leone-excited-about-her-Tamil-film/articleshow/26402212.cms |title=Sunny Leone excited about her Tamil film \u2013 Times Of India |publisher=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date=2013-11-26 |accessdate=2013-12-05}}</ref> She next appeared in the item number ''Pink Lips'' for the film ''[[Hate Story 2]]'', .<ref>{{cite news|title=Sunny Leone's Pink Lips gets 10 lakhs fans|url=http://www.patrika.com/article/sunny-leones-pink-lips-gets-10-lakhs-fans/47503|accessdate=8 July 2014|work=Patrika Group|date=7 July 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140713011726/http://www.patrika.com/article/sunny-leones-pink-lips-gets-10-lakhs-fans/47503|archivedate=July 13, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> After giving a hit number ''Pink Lips'', she appeared once again in ''Shake That Booty'' opposite [[Mika Singh]] from his film ''[[Balwinder Singh Famous Ho Gaya]]''. She made her acting debut in the [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film industry by appearing in a cameo in ''[[Current Theega]]'' opposite [[Manchu Manoj]] and [[Rakul Preet Singh]] where she played a school teacher.<ref name=\"timesofindia.indiatimes.com\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/First-look-Sunny-Leone-stuns-in-a-sari-in-Current-Theega/articleshow/37393994.cms|title=First look : Sunny Leone stuns in a sari in Current Theega|work=The Times of India|accessdate=September 22, 2014}}</ref>\n[[File:Sunny Leone snapped post shoot at Mehboob Studio 2.jpg|thumb|upright|Sunny Leone at [[Mehboob Studios]] in 2016]]\nLeone then appeared in item song ''Sesamma Bagilu Tegiyamma'' in [[Kannada language|Kannada]] film ''[[DK (film)|DK]]'', which marked her debut in Kannada film industry.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sunny Leone to do item number for DK|url=http://www.patrika.com/article/sunny-leone-to-do-item-number-for-dk/48255|accessdate=5 August 2014|work=Patrika Group|issue=5 August 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808022021/http://www.patrika.com/article/sunny-leone-to-do-item-number-for-dk/48255|archivedate=August 8, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In April 2015,  Leone appeared in Bobby Khan's musical thriller ''[[Leela (2015 film)|Ek Paheli Leela]]'', where she portrayed dual roles as Leela, a village belle and Meera, a supermodel from Milan. The film was released on April 10, 2015.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sunny Leone's hot and desi look in Leela|url=http://www.patrika.com/article/sunny-leones-hot-and-desi-look-in-leela/48131|accessdate=31 July 2014|work=Patrika Group|issue=31 July 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140802135019/http://www.patrika.com/article/sunny-leones-hot-and-desi-look-in-leela/48131|archivedate=August 2, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-review/Ek-Paheli-Leela/movie-review/46877692.cms|title=Ek Paheli Leela Movie Review|work=The Times of India}}</ref> The film met with mixed to negative reviews but was a commercial success with collections of  {{INRConvert|27.47|c}}.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ek Paheli Leela : 1st Wednesday (Day 6) Box Office Collections |url=http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/ek-paheli-leela-1st-wedneday-day-6-box-office-collections |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150418124845/http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/ek-paheli-leela-1st-wedneday-day-6-box-office-collections/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=April 18, 2015 |accessdate=17 April 2015 |work=Koimoi.com |issue=17 April 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Box Office Capsule \"Ek Paheli Leela\"|url=http://www.boxofficecapsule.com/analysis/Lifetime-Business--Economics-Of-EK-PAHELI-LEELA-3555|access-date=May 4, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160329155314/http://www.boxofficecapsule.com/analysis/Lifetime-Business--Economics-Of-EK-PAHELI-LEELA-3555|archive-date=March 29, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> After a little gap, post the release of ''Ek Paheli Leela '', she appeared in Devang Dholakia's ''[[Kuch Kuch Locha Hai]]'' was released on May 8, 2015. She essayed the role of a film star opposite [[Ram Kapoor]], [[Evelyn Sharma]] and Navdeep Chabbra. The film emerged to be a critical and commercial failure.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sunny gives another sex comedy|url=http://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Sunny-Leone-Ram-Kapoor-display-their-comic-side-in-Kuch-Kuch-Locha-Hai/articleshow/45317764.cms}}</ref> She did her second Kannada song \"Kamakshi\" from the film ''Luv U Alia''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sunny Leone in her second Kannada film|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/sunny-leone-in-special-cameo-in-luv-u-alia/}}</ref> Last in 2015, she appeared in a cameo in [[Akshay Kumar]]'s ''[[Singh is Bling]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sunny Leone shoots for a cameo in Singh is Bling|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/15001442/Sunny-Leone-does-a-cameo-in-Akshay-Kumars-Singh-Is-Bliing}}</ref> \nIn January 2016, she appeared in [[Milap Zaveri]]'s adult comedy ''[[Mastizaade]]'', released on January 29, 2016 where she portrayed twin sisters, Laila Lele and Lily Lele along with [[Tusshar Kapoor]] and [[Vir Das]]. The film released to mixed reviews and was an average earner.<ref name=\"indiatoday.intoday.in\">{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/sunny-leone--sex-comedy-mastizaade-milap-zaveri/1/358490.html|title=First poster of Sunny Leone's sex-comedy Mastizaade out|publisher=|accessdate=September 22, 2014}}</ref> One critic said \"Leone may not be better than this film, but she's the best thing in it.\"<ref name=LATimes2016/> Her next film was Jasmine D'souza's ''[[One Night Stand (2015 film)|One Night Stand]]'' with [[Tanuj Virwani]] released on May 6, 2016. The film was released to mixed reviews but was a flop commercially.<ref>{{cite news|title=One Night Stand commences shoot|url=http://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/Sunny-Leones-One-Night-Stand-in-Thailand/photostory/46128243.cms|work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=[[Bennett, Coleman & Co. Ltd.]]|date=February 5, 2015}}</ref> Her last release of 2016 was Rajeev Chaudary's ''[[Beiimaan Love]]'' opposite [[Rajneesh Duggal]] that released on October 14, 2016. Her performance was widely praised but the film met with negative reviews and flopped.<ref>{{cite news|title=Beiimaan Love kickstarts with cake cutting|url=http://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Rajneesh-Duggal-excited-to-team-up-with-Sunny-Leone-again-in-Tera-Beimaan-Love/articleshow/46930829.cms}}{{Dead link|date=June 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=no }}</ref> She also appeared in song \"Tu Zaroorat Nahi Tu Zaroori Hai\" with [[Sharman Joshi]] in ''[[Fuddu]]'' and item song \"Choli Blockbuster\" for the film ''Dongri Ka Raja''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sunny gets a new voice for item number|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-mamta-sharma-to-sing-an-item-number-for-sunny-leone-2260735|work=[[Dna India]]|publisher=[[Diligent Media Corporation]]|date=October 3, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Sunny and Sharman to steamup the song|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/sunny-leone-sizzles-ranbir-kapoor-sharman-joshi-song-video-teaser-released-693982|work=[[IB Times]] India|date=September 16, 2016}}</ref> In December 2016, her song \"Laila Main Laila\" from ''[[Raees (film)|Raees]]'' with [[Shah Rukh Khan]] was released.<ref>{{cite news|title='Raees' rail ride: Sunny Leone shocked by the fan frenzy at Vadodara station|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/raees-rail-ride-sunny-leone-shocked-by-the-fan-frenzy-at-vadodara-station/articleshow/56742559.cms|work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=[[Bennett, Coleman & Co. Ltd.]]|date=January 25, 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Sunny Leone promotes Raees-2.jpg|thumb|left|Sunny Leone at an event promotion of ''[[Raees (film)|Raees]]'' in 2017]]\nIn April 2017, she appeared in a cameo for [[Sonakshi Sinha]]'s ''[[Noor (film)|Noor]]'' where she is portrayed the role of an actress.{{citation needed|date=March 2019}} She then appeared in song \"Piya More\" with [[Emraan Hashmi]] in [[Milan Luthria]]'s ''[[Baadshaho]]''.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Sunny-Leone-to-groove-with-Ajay-Devgn-in-Baadshaho/articleshow/53633130.cms\"Sunny|title=Leone to groove with Ajay Devgn in 'Baadshaho'|work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=[[Bennett, Coleman & Co. Ltd.]]|date=January 28, 2017|accessdate=October 14, 2017}}</ref> In addition, she appeared in song \"Trippy Trippy\" in [[Sanjay Dutt|Sanjay Dutt's]] comeback film, ''[[Bhoomi (film)|Bhoomi]]'' released on September 22, 2017.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sunny Leone to do a song in Sanjay Dutt's comeback film|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/after-shah-rukh-khan-and-emraan-hashmi-sunny-leone-to-shoot-a-special-song-for-sanjay-dutts-comeback-film-bhoomi/|work=[[BollywoodLife.com]]|date=July 25, 2017|last=Chauhan|first=Gaurang}}</ref> She also made her [[Marathi Cinema|Marathi]] and [[Cinema of West Bengal|Bengali]] film debuts the same month with songs \"Kuth Kuth Jayacha Honeymoon La\" in Vishal Devrukhkar's ''[[Boyz (film)|Boyz]]'' and \"Chaap Nishna\" in [[Swapan Saha]]'s ''[[Shrestha Bangali]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sunny makes Marathi debut with an item song|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/videos/kuth-kuth-jayacha-honeymoon-la-sunny-leone-boyz-marathi-movie.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Sunny in Sera Bangali|url=http://m.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/in-pics-sunny-leone-makes-bengali-debut-with-rajpal-yadav-in-sera-bengali/story-iB3ekeeUQwX9KZZ6rrz4uO.html|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|publisher=[[HT Media]]|date=July 26, 2017}}</ref> She then appeared in song \"Deo Deo\" for [[Rajasekhar (actor)|Rajasekhar]]'s Telugu film ''[[PSV Garuda Vega]]''<ref>{{cite news|title=Sunny Leone signs secong Telugu film|url=http://www.news18.com/news/movies/sunny-leone-was-my-first-choice-for-special-number-in-psv-garuda-vega-praveen-sattaru-1358065.html|work=[[News18 India]]|publisher=[[Network18 Group]]|date=March 9, 2017}}</ref> Her last appearance was her mainstream film ''[[Tera Intezaar]]'' along [[Arbaaz Khan]] directed by Rajeev Walia. The film released on 1 December 2017.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sunny Leone excited to work with Arbaaz Khan|url=http://m.indiatoday.in/story/sunny-leone-new-film-arbaaz-khan-malaika-arora-divorce/1/680882.html|work=[[India Today]]|publisher=[[Living Media]]|date=May 30, 2016}}</ref>\n\nSunny Leone was voted by the Network 7 Media Group jury as \"Indian Affairs Actress of the year 2018\" founded by Satya Brahma at the historic 9th Annual [[India Leadership Conclave]] & Indian Affairs Business Leadership Awards 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://indialeadershipconclave.info/sunny-leone-honored-as-indian-affairs-actress-of-the-year-2018-at-india-leadership-conclave-2018/|title=Sunny Leone honored as \u201cIndian Affairs Actress of the year 2018\u201d at India Leadership Conclave 2018|date=2018-07-26|work=India Leadership Conclave 2018|access-date=2018-08-04|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n=== Upcoming projects ===\nIn January 2018, Leone started filming for the Hindi remake of 2012 [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]] film ''[[Jatt & Juliet]]''  opposite [[Manish Paul]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sunny Leone in Jatt And Juliet remake|url=http://m.filmfare.com/news/sunny-leone-in-jatt-and-juliet-remake-12860.html}}</ref> She is also set to star in ''[[Veeramadevi]]'' a period war Tamil film in full-fledged lead role directed by V.C. Vadivudaiyan. The shooting for the film will commence in February 2018 and will be released in Telugu, Hindi & [[Malayalam language|Malayalam]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sunny Leone to make Tamil debut|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/sunny-leone-first-kollywood-film-as-a-leading-lady-titled-veeramadevi-see-photo-5002286/}}</ref>\nSunny Leone's auto biopic titled \"[[Karenjit Kaur \u2013 The Untold Story of Sunny Leone]]\", an original web-series by [[ZEE5]],<ref>{{cite web|author=Back to |url=https://www.zee5.com/zee5originals/details/karenjit-kaur-the-untold-story-of-sunny-leone/0-6-tvshow_984782182 |title='Karenjit Kaur \u2013 the untold story of Sunny Leone |publisher=zee5.com |date= |accessdate=2018-06-29}}</ref> was released on the platform on 16 July 2018.<ref>{{cite news|title=Watch: Sunny Leone unveils the 38-second motion poster of her biopic Karenjit Kaur & it breaks the Internet in 24 hours|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-watch-sunny-leone-unveils-the-38-second-motion-poster-of-her-biopic-karenjit-kaur-it-breaks-the-internet-in-24-hours-2632441}}</ref> The series narrates her journey from a [[middle-class]] girl in Canada to becoming India's most googled celebrity. The series starts from her childhood as Gogu to her foray into the adult film industry to her exciting journey into [[Bollywood]]. The series will also be available in [[Bengali language|Bengali]], [[Tamil language|Tamil]], [[Telugu language|Telugu]] and [[Marathi language|Marathi]] languages.\n\n== Writer ==\n''Sweet Dreams'' is a collection of 12 short stories written by Sunny Leone.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thequint.com/entertainment/2016/04/22/sunny-leone-writes-her-first-short-story-collection-sweet-dreams|title=Sunny Leone Writes Her First Short Story Collection - Sweet Dreams|last=|first=|date=22 April 2016|website=The Quint|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://epaper.indianexpress.com/c/9859346|title=Love, the Sunny Leone way|date=2016-04-23|website=The Indian Express|access-date=2016-04-23}}</ref> They were published digitally as an e-book and launched on 22 April 2016 by [[Juggernaut Books]] through their mobile app.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/lifestyle/what-s-hot/story/sunny-leone-first-book-erotica-erotic-literature-sweet-dreams-319372-2016-04-22|title=Sunny Leone's first book is everything you'd expect it to be|last=|first=|date=29 April 2019|website=India Today|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref> A story was made available on the app at 10pm every night.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Sunny-Leone-to-share-her-stories-on-your-phone-every-night/articleshow/51927942.cms|title=Sunny Leone to share her stories on your phone every night!|last=|first=|date=28 January 2017|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref> A 200 page paperback edition was also launched in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amazon.in/Sweet-Dreams-Sunny-Leone/dp/8193237226/ref=tmm_pap_swatch_0?_encoding=UTF8&qid=&sr=|title=Sweet Dreams|last=Leone|first=Sunny|date=6 June 2016|website=Amazon|access-date=30 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe work was well received by the ''[[Hindustan Times]]'', which commented, \"Sunny's stories are relentlessly optimistic. The characters are not complicated or unpleasant and exist in a world that veers on the border of Valentine's Land with its floating pink hearts and soft focus lighting.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/books/sunny-leone-reveals-what-her-erotic-short-stories-will-be-like/story-MHkkB8H28HYBYb8wiYGc1O.html|title=Sunny Leone reveals what her erotic short stories will be like|date=2016-04-23|website=hindustantimes.com|access-date=2016-04-23}}</ref>\n\nSunny Leone in an interview to [[Press Trust of India]] explains that the book is written from the perspective of both men and females, as well as being written for both genders but mainly for women; \"I wrote these stories, from what I thought a woman would like to read.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theweek.in/content/archival/news/entertainment/sunny-leone-turns-writer-pens-short-stories.html|title=Sunny Leone turns writer|last=|first=|date=23 April 2016|website=theweek.in|access-date=2019-11-29}}{{dead link|date=March 2020|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> Sunny Leone add that it is \"the first time (she has) written something like this.\"<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-sweet-dreams-after-acting-sunny-leone-turns-writer-pens-short-stories-2205308|title=Sweet Dreams: After acting, Sunny Leone turns writer, pens short stories|last=|first=|date=23 April 2016|website=DNA India|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref> In the interview she mentioned how [[Juggernaut Books]] had come to her with this idea of writing the book.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nSweet Dreams was [[Elle (India)|Elle's]] 'Book of the Week' in April 2016 and in the review they go on to write \"don\u2019t go looking for creative fantasies or fetishes; as a writer, Leone is playing safe.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://elle.in/article/book-of-the-week-sweet-dreams-by-sunny-leone/|title=Book of the week: Sweet Dreams by Sunny Leone|last=|first=|date=22 April 2016|website=Elle India|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref> Another review in [[Bollywood Hungama]] goes on to note if there was any real contribution from Sunny herself towards the book other than her picture on the cover. The review goes on say that there is \"no note by (the) author, acknowledgments section, or forward from some known entity.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.freepressjournal.in/book-reviews/sunny-leones-sweet-dreams|title=Sunny Leone\u2019s Sweet Dreams|last=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|first=|date=|website=Free Press Journal|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bgr.in/news/sunny-leone-turns-author-with-juggernaut-new-e-books-app-launched-for-android-401703/|title=Sunny Leone turns author with Juggernaut, new e-books app launched for Android|last=Bhushan|first=Kul|date=2016-04-22|website=BGR India|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\n== Activism ==\n[[File:Sunny Leone launches PETA - Adopt a stray dog campaign 2.jpg|thumb|Leone at the [[PETA]]'s stray dog adoption campaign]]\nIn 2004, she was part of ''No More Bush Girls'', in which she and several other popular adult actresses shaved off their [[pubic hair]] in protest of the [[George W. Bush]] presidency.<ref name=\"shave2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ncbuy.com/news/2004-10-15/1010837.html|title=Porn Stars Shave To Support 'No More Bush' Campaign|author=Wireless Flash News|date=2004-10-15|publisher=Wireless Flash News|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20041017020125/http://www.ncbuy.com/news/2004-10-15/1010837.html|archive-date=2004-10-17|url-status=dead|accessdate=2004-10-15}}</ref> In May 2008, she shot a promotional video for [[Declare Yourself]], a nonprofit, nonpartisan voter registration campaign targeting 18- to 29-year-olds.<ref name=\"votepsa2\">{{cite web|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/30415.html|title=Sunny Leone Urges Youth to Vote in Online PSA|author=David Sullivan|date=2008-05-27|publisher=AVN|accessdate=2008-05-27}}</ref> She indicated that [[Barack Obama]] would be her choice in the 2008 U.S. presidential election, primarily because she felt he was more business friendly to the adult industry than his opponent [[John McCain]].<ref name=\"elect2\">{{cite web|url=http://metallungies.com/2008/09/metallungies-hollers-savanna-samson-and-sunny-leone-interview/|title=Metallungies Hollers @ Savanna Samson and Sunny Leone, Interview|author=knobbz|date=2008-09-13|publisher=metallungies.com|accessdate=2008-12-25}}</ref> She also released a public service announcement on behalf of the ASACP, reminding adult webmasters to protect their sites from children by having an RTA label on it.\n\nIn 2013, Leone posed for a [[People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals|PETA]] ad campaign, encouraging dog and cat owners to have their pets spayed and neutered. In an interview for PETA India, Leone said, \"I believe that every single dog should be spayed and neutered. You don't want to continue the cycle of homeless dogs or cats. And spaying and neutering also keeps them healthy.\"<ref>[http://www.asianimage.co.uk/news/10161044.Sunny_Leone_in_new_PETA_ad/ Sunny Leone In New PETA Ad]\", Asian Image, 15 January 2013.</ref> PETA named her their \"Person of the Year\" in 2016.<ref>\"[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/sunny-leone-to-receive-petas-person-of-the-year-award/articleshow/56123031.cms Sunny Leone To Receive PETA's Person of the Year Award],\" ''Times of India'', 22 December 2016.</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn June 2006, Leone became an American citizen,<ref name=\"xrent\"/> but stated she planned to remain a [[dual citizen]] of Canada.<ref name=\"sapna\">{{cite web |url=http://www.sapnamagazine.com/fall05/articles/culture/fa-sunny.html |title=Sex and Stardom: Inside the World of a Desi Adult Entertainer |accessdate=2007-08-22 |author=Shaheryar Hafeez |date=Fall 2005 |work=[[Sapna magazine]]}}</ref> On 14 April 2012, Leone announced that she was now a resident of India<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/SunnyLeone/status/191135558796451841 |title=Twitter / SunnyLeone: I have the greatest news today |publisher=Twitter.com |date= |accessdate=2013-11-02}}</ref><ref name=\"in.movies.yahoo.com\">{{cite web |url=http://in.movies.yahoo.com/news/sunny-leone-now-indian-citizen-183000530.html |title=Sunny Leone Now An Indian Citizen \u2013 Yahoo Movies India |publisher=In.movies.yahoo.com |date=2012-04-14 |accessdate=2013-11-02 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105050026/http://in.movies.yahoo.com/news/sunny-leone-now-indian-citizen-183000530.html |archivedate=November 5, 2013 |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref name=\"in.movies.yahoo.com\"/> explaining in an interview to ''[[The New Indian Express]]'' that she was an [[Overseas Citizen of India]] and that she was eligible for overseas citizenship because her parents lived in [[India]]. She applied for it prior to filming ''Jism 2''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Bansal |first=Varsha |url=http://newindianexpress.com/entertainment/interviews/article585734.ece |title=Sunny Leone, about Indian fans |publisher=The New Indian Express |date=2012-08-15 |accessdate=2013-11-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://daily.bhaskar.com/article/MAH-MUM-sunny-leone-ragini-mms-2-later-house-in-mumbai-first-3669421.html |title=Sunny Leone: Ragini MMS 2 later, house in Mumbai first |publisher=daily.bhaskar.com |date=2012-08-20 |accessdate=2013-11-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-triple-treat-sunny-leone-will-have-three-releases-within-the-next-six-months-1917049 |title=Triple treat! Sunny Leone will have three releases within the next six months \u2013 Entertainment \u2013 DNA |publisher=Dnaindia.com |date= 2013-11-11|accessdate=2013-12-05}}</ref><ref name=\"rta2\">{{cite web|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/33070.html|title=Sunny Leone RTA PSA to Debut at AVN Awards|author=AVN Staff|date=January 7, 2009|publisher=AVN|accessdate=January 7, 2009}}</ref>\n\nLeone has a strong interest in health and fitness, and has been featured in several mainstream fitness publications. Leone has modelled fitness clothing for the sports brand Fantasy Fitness<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fantasyfitness.com/models/sunny-leone.php|title=Sunny Leone models with Fantasy Fitness|author=Fantasy Fitness|date=2009-08-01|publisher=FantasyFitness.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090721115016/http://www.fantasyfitness.com/models/sunny-leone.php|archive-date=July 21, 2009|url-status=dead|accessdate=2009-08-01|df=}}</ref> and shared that she keeps her body in shape by working out as much as she can despite her busy schedule and as quoted in ''[[Men's Fitness]]'' magazine, \"I try to eat very healthy&nbsp;\u2013 lots of vegetables, drinking my milk every day.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mensfitness.com/advice/hot-women/meet-girl-sunny-leone|title=Adult star Sunny Leone loves playing the field|author=Men's Fitness|date=2009-08-01|publisher=[[Men's Fitness]]|accessdate=2009-08-01}}</ref>\n\nAlthough bisexual, she has stated that she prefers men.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiavision.com/news/article/lifestyle/252006/bigg-boss-sunny-leone-is-bisexual-but-prefers-men/|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130126074309/http://www.indiavision.com/news/article/lifestyle/252006/bigg-boss-sunny-leone-is-bisexual-but-prefers-men/|url-status=dead|archive-date=2013-01-26|title=Bigg Boss' Sunny Leone is bisexual, but prefers men|date=2011-11-25|publisher=Indiavision news}}</ref> Sunny Leone had dated Indian-Canadian stand-up comedian [[Russell Peters]] up until they broke up in 2007.<ref>{{cite web |title=Comedian Russell Peters Goes Off on Trevor Noah + Names His Top 5 Comedians |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aGXWYomn_6s |website=[[YouTube]] |publisher=[[Sway Calloway|Sway's Universe]] |accessdate=July 27, 2018 |date=June 28, 2018 |minutes=12}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Goyal|first=Samarth|title=Sunny Leone is a real sweetheart: Russell Peters|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/tabloid/sunny-leone-is-a-real-sweetheart-russell-peters/article1-1140756.aspx|accessdate=29 October 2013|newspaper=Hindustan Times|date=September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Sunny Leone dated comedian Russell Peters?|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Sunny-Leone-dated-comedian-Russell-Peters/articleshow/24928353.cms|accessdate=29 October 2013|newspaper=Times of India|date=September 2013}}</ref> Leone was then dating Matt Erikson, a vice-president of marketing at [[Playboy Enterprises]]. After being engaged to Erikson, they broke up in 2008.<ref name=\"torostar\">{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/DesiLife/article/265411/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071012213649/http://www.thestar.com/DesiLife/article/265411 |url-status=dead |archive-date=October 12, 2007 |title=Sunny Leone on life as a desi adult star |accessdate=2007-10-26 |author=Sonia M. Kandathil |date=2007-10-11 |publisher=[[Toronto Star]] |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-12-24/tv/30551502_1_sunny-bigg-boss-house-movies|archive-url=https://archive.today/20131031012251/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-12-24/tv/30551502_1_sunny-bigg-boss-house-movies|url-status=dead|archive-date=2013-10-31|title=Sunny Leone's ex making moolah off her|accessdate=2012-10-26|author=Tushar Joshi|date=2007-10-11|publisher=Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/daniel-weber-sunny-leone-bigg-boss-matt-erikson/1/166987.html|title=I want to marry Daniel Weber over and over again: Sunny Leone|accessdate=2012-10-26|author=|date=2007-10-11|publisher=[[India Today]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Tabloid/Sunny-Leone-s-ex-cashes-in-on-her-fame/Article1-786520.aspx|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111224103536/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Tabloid/Sunny-Leone-s-ex-cashes-in-on-her-fame/Article1-786520.aspx|url-status=dead|archive-date=2011-12-24|title=Sunny Leone's ex cashes in on her fame|accessdate=2012-10-26|author=|date=2007-10-11|publisher=Hindustan Times}}</ref> She mentioned in an interview at the start of 2011 that she was married to Daniel Weber.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.movieweb.com/news/exclusive-sunny-leone-talks-the-virginity-hit|title=EXCLUSIVE: Sunny Leone Talks The Virginity Hit|first=B. Alan|last=Orange|work=movieweb.com|date=2011-01-17|accessdate=2011-12-24}}</ref> During her stay in the ''Bigg Boss'' house later that same year, Leone indicated that she had married; Leone said she \"purposely arrived late\" to their first date as she was not impressed with him, but he changed her mind by sending 24 roses to her hotel room.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiavision.com/news/article/entertainment/254769/sunny-leone-breaks-hearts-by-getting-married-in-bigg-boss-house/|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130126232911/http://www.indiavision.com/news/article/entertainment/254769/sunny-leone-breaks-hearts-by-getting-married-in-bigg-boss-house/|url-status=dead|archive-date=2013-01-26|title=Sunny Leone breaks hearts by getting 'married' in Bigg Boss house|date=2011-12-03|publisher=Indiavision news}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Team|first=Businessofcinema.com|title=Sunny Leone's Husband: Proud Of Her Bollywood Debut|url=http://businessofcinema.com/news/sunny-leones-husband-proud-bollywood-debut/|accessdate=August 6, 2012|newspaper=Businessofcinema.com|date=August 3, 2012}}</ref>\n\nA 2008 ''[[Eye Weekly]]'' article reported that \"Leone does her best to maintain a link to Sikh traditions, even if more in theory than in practice. But she's unlikely to disavow her career path due to religion\" and that Leone said \"Girls will leave the industry claiming that they found God. Well, the fact is, God has always been with them the entire time.\"<ref name=EyeWeekly>{{cite web|url=http://www.eyeweekly.com/scrollingeye/article/32910|title=Sunny Leone's America|last=Weisblott|first=Marc|date=2009-07-04|publisher=[[Eye Weekly]]|accessdate=2009-01-20|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110710213113/http://www.eyeweekly.com/scrollingeye/article/32910|archivedate=2011-07-10|url-status=dead}}</ref> In a 2010 interview, she said\n\n<blockquote>It's a community-based religion. You walk into a temple and you're greeted with the utmost respect... But, just like any religion it doesn't want you to shoot adult material. I mean, I grew up going to temple every Sunday. When my parents found out they knew my personality which was very independent. Even if they tried to stop me or tried to steer me the right way they would have lost their daughter. I'm too headstrong. And it wasn't a plan. It just happened and my career and everything just kept getting bigger and bigger.<ref name=Alff/></blockquote>\n\n[[File:Sunny Leone & Daniel Weber graces Vogue Beauty Awards 2017.jpg|thumb|left|Sunny Leone and her husband Daniel Weber at Vogue Beauty Awards in 2017]]\nIn July 2017, Leone and her husband Daniel Weber adopted their first child from [[Latur]], a village in [[Maharashtra]]. The baby girl, whom they named Nisha Kaur Weber, was 21 months old at the time of adoption. Actress [[Sherlyn Chopra]] first confirmed the news by writing a congratulatory message on social media on 20 July 2017. \"Never in my life did I think that I want to adopt a child. People doing such amazing work at the orphanage changed my mind,\" Daniel Weber told [[Hindustan Times]].\"<ref name=NDTV>{{cite web|url=http://www.ndtv.com/india-news/sunny-leone-and-husband-daniel-weber-adopt-baby-girl-1727387|title=\nSunny Leone And Husband Daniel Weber Adopt Baby Girl|work=[[NDTV 24x7|NDTV]]|accessdate=2017-07-22}}</ref><ref name=\"The Indian Express\">{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/sunny-leone-and-daniel-weber-adopt-daughter-nisha-confirmed-see-photos-4761395/|title=\nSunny Leone and Daniel Weber adopt baby girl, see first photos of Nisha Kaur Weber|work=[[The Indian Express]]|publisher=[[Indian Express Group]]|accessdate=2017-07-22|date=2017-07-21}}</ref><ref name=TOI>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/sunny-leone-adopts-baby-girl-nisha/articleshow/59692469.cms|title=\nSunny Leone and husband Daniel Weber adopts baby girl Nisha|work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=[[Bennett, Coleman & Co. Ltd.]]|accessdate=2017-07-22}}</ref><ref name=Firstpost>{{cite web|url=http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/sunny-leone-daniel-weber-adopt-baby-girl-from-latur-name-her-nisha-kaur-weber-3839393.html|title=\nSunny Leone, Daniel Weber adopt baby girl from Latur, name her Nisha Kaur Weber|work=[[Firstpost]]|accessdate=2017-07-22|date=2017-07-21}}</ref>\n\nOn March 4, 2018, Sunny Leone and her husband announced the birth of their twin boys, born through [[surrogacy]]. They named the boys Asher Singh Weber and Noah Singh Weber.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://economictimes.com/magazines/panache/sunny-leone-announces-birth-of-twins-tweets-about-it/articleshow/63167825.cms|title=Sunny Leone announces birth of twins, tweets about it|accessdate=2018-03-05|work=[[The Economic Times]]|publisher=[[Bennett, Coleman & Co. Ltd.]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bombaytimes.com/celebs/sunny-leone-and-daniel-weber-become-parents-for-the-second-time/articleshow/63167458.cms|title=Sunny Leone and Daniel Weber become parents for the second time|work=[[Bombay Times]]|publisher=[[Bennett, Coleman & Co. Ltd.]]|accessdate=2018-03-05}}</ref>\n\nLeone lives in [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]]. She moved into their new house with husband Weber and children on [[Ganesh Chaturthi]] which fell on September 13, 2018.<ref name=\"NDTVGaneshChaturthi\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/ganesh-chaturthi-2018-sunny-leone-and-husband-daniel-weber-celebrate-by-moving-into-new-home-1915997|title=Ganesh Chaturthi 2018: Sunny Leone And Husband Daniel Weber Celebrate By Moving Into New Home|work=[[NDTV 24x7|NDTV]]|accessdate=September 16, 2018|date=September 13, 2018|last=Shiksha|first=Shruti}}</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\nA police [[first information report]] was filed against her in May 2015 after a woman at [[Mumbai]], India, complained that Leone's website, sunnyleone.com, was destroying the Indian culture. Thane police's cyber cell at Ramnagar booked her for sections 292, 292A, 294 which could land her a term in jail, fine or both. Senior police inspector JK Sawant stated, \"We cannot block the website, but will ask the operator to remove objectionable content.\"<ref name=\"FIR\">{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Mumbai-woman-files-FIR-against-Leone-for-destroying-Indian-culture/articleshow/47303642.cms|title=Mumbai woman files FIR against Leone for 'destroying Indian culture'|last=Pradeep Gupta|date=2015-05-16|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=23 August 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn the 2017 new year, a pro-[[Kannada]] group Rakshana Vedike Yuva Sene protested against the event ''Sunny Night in Bengaluru NYE 2018'' in [[Bangalore]]. Sunny Leone was to perform at this event and the group argued that due to her pornographic past, she shouldn't be allowed in the event. The protesters threatened a [[mass suicide]] and Karnataka home minister [[Ramalinga Reddy]] denied her permission to appear at the event.<ref>{{cite news|title=Karnataka government denies permission to Sunny Leone's New Year's Eve event|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/karnataka-government-denies-permission-sunny-leones-new-years-eve-event/|accessdate=26 March 2018|work=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|date=16 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, a social activist lodged a complaint against Leone at the Nazarethpet police station in [[Chennai]]. He stated that the actress is promoting pornography which is against the Indian nation's law. He also added that this will majorly dent the Indian culture and spoil the moral fabric of the society.<ref>{{cite news|title=FIR filed against Sunny Leone for promoting pornography|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/fir-filed-sunny-leone-promoting-pornography/|accessdate=26 March 2018|work=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|date=10 February 2018}}</ref>\n\nProducer and distributor Bharat Patel has accused Leone of not returning a signing fee which she had taken to do a special dance number for his movie [[Patel Ki Punjabi Shaadi]] after her role was cancelled.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sunny Leone accused of not returning signing amount by 'Patel Ki Punjabi Shaadi' producer|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/sunny-leone-accused-of-not-returning-signing-amount-by-patel-ki-punjabi-shaadi-producer/articleshow/67656731.cms|accessdate=24 January 2019|work=[[Times of India]]|date=16 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n{{Main|Filmography and awards of Sunny Leone}}\n\n== Bibliography ==\n* ''Sweet Dreams'' (2016)\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Bollywood|Erotica and pornography}}\n* [[List of pornographic actors who appeared in mainstream films]]\n* [[Pornography in India]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Sunny Leone}}\n* {{Official website}} ({{small|pornography}})\n* {{Official website|sunnyleoneofficial.com}} ({{small|mainstream}})\n* {{IMDb name}}\n* {{IAFD name}}\n* {{afdb name}}\n* [http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrity/sunny-leone/ Sunny Leone] at [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes person|sunny_leone|Sunny Leone}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Penthouse Pets of 2001}}\n{{Penthouse Pets of 2003}}\n{{Pets of the Year}}\n{{Bigg Boss}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Leone, Sunny}}\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresse