{"title_page": "I Can See Your Voice (South Korean season 7)", "text_new": "{{redirect|I Can See Your Voice Lucky 7|other uses|Lucky 7}}\n{{Infobox television season \n| bgcolour             = blue\n| season_name          = ''I Can See Your Voice'' (South Korean season 7)<br>{{small|{{lang|ko|\ub108\uc758 \ubaa9\uc18c\ub9ac\uac00 \ubcf4\uc5ec 7}}}}\n| season_number        = 7\n| image                =  \n| image_alt            =  \n| caption              =  \n| module1              = {{Infobox reality competition season\n | presenter           = {{plainlist|*[[Kim Jong-kook (singer)|Kim Jong-kook]]\n*[[Leeteuk]]\n*[[Yoo Se-yoon]] \n}}\n | judges              = {{plainlist|\n*[[Click-B#Kim Sang-hyuk|Kim Sang-hyuk]]\n*[[Lee Sang-min (singer)|Lee Sang-min]]\n*[[Joon Park]] ([[g.o.d]])\n*[[DinDin]]\n*{{illm|Hong Yoon-hwa|ko|\ud64d\uc724\ud654}}\n*[[Sleepy (rapper)|Sleepy]] ([[Untouchable (South Korean band)|Untouchable]])\n}}\n}}\n | country              = South Korea\n | num_episodes         = 11\n | network              = {{plainlist|*[[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]] (Original)\n*[[TVN (South Korean TV channel)|tvN (South Korea)]] (Simulcast)\n*[[TVN (Asian TV channel)|tvN Asia]] (Southeast Asia)\n}}\n | first_aired          = {{Start date|2020|01|17}}\n | last_aired           = present\n| prev_season          = [[I Can See Your Voice (South Korean season 6)|Season 6 (2019)]]\n| next_season          = \n}}\n\nThe '''seventh season''' of the South Korean mystery music game show '''''[[I Can See Your Voice (South Korean TV series)|I Can See Your Voice]]''''', also known as '''''I Can See Your Voice Lucky 7''''',<ref>{{Cite news|author=Lee Jeong-hyun|title=\uad6d\ub0b4\uc678 \ud640\ub9b0 '\ub108\uc758 \ubaa9\uc18c\ub9ac\uac00 \ubcf4\uc5ec' \uc2dc\uc98c7 \uc628\ub2e4|url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20191212048800005|website=[[Yonhap]]|date=December 12, 2019|accessdate=December 23, 2019|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|author=Kim Soo-kyung|title='\ub108\ubaa9\ubcf47', 2020\ub144 1\uc6d4 17\uc77c \uccab\ubc29...\uc2a4\ud3ec\uce20 \uc2a4\ud0c0\ub3c4 \ucd9c\uc5f0\ud55c\ub2e4|url=https://www.hankyung.com/entertainment/article/2019122355054|website=[[Korea Economic Daily]]|date=December 23, 2019|accessdate=December 23, 2019|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1371080wpp/i-can-see-your-voice-announces-season-7-premiere-date-return-of-kim-jong-kook-super-juniors-leeteuk-and-yoo-se-yoon-as-mcs|title=\"I Can See Your Voice\" Announces Season 7 Premiere Date + Return Of Kim Jong Kook, Super Junior's Leeteuk, And Yoo Se Yoon As MCs|date=December 12, 2019|website=[[Soompi]]|language=en|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref> premiered on January 17, 2020 on [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]] and is simulcast on [[TVN (South Korean TV channel)|tvN in South Korea]]. It airs six days later on [[TVN (Asian TV channel)|tvN Asia]].<ref name=\"tvN Asia Sched 23-01-2020\">{{Cite web |url=https://tvnasia.net/schedule/?country=philippines&timezone=8&date=23-01-2020 |title=SCHEDULE \u2013 tvN \u2013 Asia {{!}} Official Page |language=en-US |access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n==Rounds==\nUnder the original format, the guest artist(s) can simply eliminate mystery singers after every round concluded; and the last mystery singer will do duet-perform with, otherwise the last mystery singer could perform freely without using accompanied guest artist(s). \n\nThere were six individuals or groups of mystery singers standing on the platform with its aliases to keep their identities concealed until its initial performance.\n\nThe winning good singer(s) will receive a digital single release while the winning bad singer(s) gets [[South Korean won|\u20a9]]5,000,000 ([[US dollar|$]]4,500).\n\n;''Round 1: Singer's visual''\nEach mystery singer is given two identities \u2013 as a good singer and as a bad singer. Only one of them is their real identity.\n\n;''Round 2: Singer's lip-sync''\nThe mystery singer lip-syncs to the good singer's voice, then the bad singer's voice comes in the middle of the performance.\n\n;''Round 3: Singer's evidence''\nThe hosts of the show have randomly assigned clues about the mystery singer. The guest artist(s) must choose a clue for each mystery singer.\n\n==Episodes==\n;''Color key''\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n{{plainlist|\n* {{Color box|#9f9|border=darkgray}} The contestant is a good singer.\n* {{Color box|#f99|border=darkgray}} The contestant is a bad singer.\n}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n{{hidden begin|expanded=true;}}\n===Guest artists===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; line-height:16px; width:100%\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" width=\"9%\"|Episode\n! rowspan=\"3\" width=\"12%\"|Guest artist\n! colspan=\"6\"|Mystery singers<br>{{small|(In their respective numbers)}}{{efn|name=\"Mystery singers\"|For the combination duo or groups, the italicized names are bad singers.}}\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"1%\"|#\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"8%\"|Date\n! colspan=\"5\"|Elimination order\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Winner\n|-\n! Visual round\n! colspan=\"2\"|Lip-sync round\n! colspan=\"2\"|Evidence round\n|-\n|-\n!1\n|''January 17, 2020''\n| [[Park Joong-hoon]]<ref>{{Cite news|author=Kim Ye-na|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] '\ub108\ubaa9\ubcf47' \ubc15\uc911\ud6c8, \uc624\ub298(2\uc77c) \uccab \ub179\ud654 '\ucd08\ub300 \uc2a4\ud0c0'\ub85c \ucd9c\uaca9|url=http://www.xportsnews.com/?ac=article_view&entry_id=1217719|website=Xports News|date=January 2, 2020|accessdate=January 13, 2020|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|author=Park So-young|title=\uccab\ubc29 '\ub108\ubaa9\ubcf47' \ubc15\uc911\ud6c8, \uc548\uc131\uae30 \uc751\uc6d0\uc5d0\ub3c4 \uc74c\uce58\uc640 \ub4c0\uc5e3 '\uc2e4\ud328'..\uc0ac\ube44\ub85c \uc120\ubb3c [\uc885\ud569]|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1111295065|website=OSEN|date=January 17, 2020|accessdate=January 17, 2020|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|author=Yoo Eun-young|title=\uccab\ubc29 '\ub108\ubaa9\ubcf47' \ubc15\uc911\ud6c8, \uc74c\uce58 \uc0c9\ucd9c \uc2e4\ud328 '\ubc18\uc804\uc5d0